info.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 01 at 2:56PM PST until February 03 at 7:00AM PST by NWS Eureka
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT FROM 7 PM THURSDAY TO 7 AM PST FRIDAY... * WHAT...Southeast winds 15 to 25 mph. The strongest gusts could reach 60 mph on exposed coastal headlands and ridges. Lower elevation gusts around Humboldt Bay and in coastal valleys will remain closer to 45 mph. * WHERE...Portions of northwest California. * WHEN...From 7 PM Thursday to 7 AM PST Friday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
